N:file-organization
D:Choose and evolve project/repository structure without cargo-culting one folder tree. Use when deciding how a frontend, backend, fullstack, docs/ops, or game-development repo should be organized; when a repo has grown messy; or when feature folders, monorepo boundaries, docs taxonomy, or engine-aware asset layouts are being debated.
G:file-organization project-structure repo-layout feature-folders monorepo naming-conventions docs-taxonomy game-development
U[6]:
  structure new repos
  refactor messy repo layout
  choose framework-default vs feature/domain mode
  define monorepo apps/packages boundaries
  organize docs/ops repositories
  organize engine-aware game/content repositories
S[5]{n,action}:
  1,Classify repository shape and growth pressure
  2,Choose one primary organization mode
  3,Define top-level boundaries and naming rules
  4,Plan incremental migration if the repo already exists
  5,Route search/automation/environment follow-ups to adjacent skills
